trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> objects.
The <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection> class provides a simple collection object that can be used to store a set of <xref:System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration> objects.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> class.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> class that contains the specified array of <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> objects.
An array of <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> objects with which to initialize the collection.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> class that contains the elements of the specified source collection.
A <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> object with which to initialize the collection.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object to the collection.
The <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object to add.
The index at which the new element was inserted.
Copies the elements of the specified array to the end of the collection.
An array of type <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> that contains the objects to add to the collection.
value is `null`.
Adds the contents of another <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> object to the end of the collection.
A <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> object that contains the objects to add to the collection.
value is `null`.
Gets a value that indicates whether the collection contains the specified <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object to search for in the collection.
`true` if the collection contains the specified object; otherwise, `false`.
Copies the elements in the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref> object to a one-dimensional <xref href="System.Array"></xref> instance, starting at the specified index.
The one-dimensional <xref href="System.Array"></xref> that is the destination of the values copied from the collection.
The index of the array at which to begin inserting.
The destination array is multidimensional.
-or-
The number of elements in the is greater than the available space between the index of the target array specified by the index parameter and the end of the target array.
The array parameter is `null`.
The index parameter is less than the target array's minimum index.

Gets the index of the specified <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object in the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclarationCollection"></xref>, if it exists in the collection.
The <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> to locate in the collection.
The index of the specified object, if it is found, in the collection; otherwise, -1.
Inserts the specified <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object into the collection at the specified index.
The zero-based index where the specified object should be inserted.
The <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object to insert.
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> object at the specified index in the collection.
This property is an indexer that can be used to access the collection.
The index of the collection to access.
A <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> at each valid index.
The index parameter is outside the valid range of indexes for the collection.

The <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeTypeDeclaration"></xref> to remove from the collection.
